	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I always understood that a ROM for a 6502 family CPU needs to return data in a half cycle. In that case, you take 500 divided by the system's clock speed. That's about 250 ns for the NES (1.8 MHz) and 120 ns for the Super NES (3.6 MHz).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


